The paper deals with data stream processing, which is a core topic in computer science. The use of Count-Min sketches and hashing functions suggests that the paper is related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the modularity property of item keys, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a new method for approximating frequency counts, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
